---
const examples = [
  {
    glyph: '{¤}',
    title: 'Friday, 2 AM. Your agent is still reading.',
    body: 'You went to bed. An abject pulled 47 papers from your RSS feeds, ranked them against your open projects, drafted a one-page summary, and pinned it to the canvas. The tokens came from your local Ollama. No surprise bill. No surprise rate limit at hour three. Wake up. Coffee. Read.',
  },
  {
    glyph: '{↻}',
    title: 'Your scraper crashed. Twenty seconds later, the work routes around it.',
    body: 'The failed task attaches its error to the goal\'s history. The next scrum reads what just broke, picks a different abject, and stages the retry. No 30-minute chain running off a cliff. The plan rewrites itself round by round.',
  },
  {
    glyph: '{△}',
    title: 'Click. Your friend\'s cursor is on your canvas.',
    body: 'She\'s in Berlin. You\'re in Brooklyn. Both on Wi-Fi. Pin a note; she draws an arrow to it; you watch her cursor move in real time. End-to-end encrypted WebRTC, ECDH key exchange, AES-256-GCM. The signaling relay never sees a byte.',
  },
  {
    glyph: '{∇}',
    title: 'Twenty words. A new program appears.',
    body: '"Watch ~/Downloads. When a PDF lands, rename it by its title, move it to ~/Papers/{year}." Chat decomposes the goal, the LLM writes the manifest, ObjectCreator spawns the abject. A new window opens. It is already running.',
  },
];
---

<section id="examples" class="examples-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">What People Build</h2>
    <p class="examples-subtitle">A handful of things abjects are good at. Some of these you can do elsewhere; all of them, here, you own.</p>

    <div class="examples-grid">
      {examples.map((e) => (
        <div class="card example-card">
          <span class="example-glyph">{e.glyph}</span>
          <h3 class="example-title">{e.title}</h3>
          <p class="example-body">{e.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="examples-footer">Three commands. One Goal. <a href="#downloads">Run it on your machine</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .examples-section {
    background: transparent;
  }

  .examples-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: -1.5rem auto 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .examples-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .examples-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .example-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .example-glyph {
    display: inline-block;
    align-self: flex-start;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--eldritch);
    background: var(--eldritch-glow);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-accent);
    padding: 0.35rem 0.55rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .example-title {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .example-body {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .examples-footer {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .examples-footer a {
    color: var(--eldritch-dim);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(43, 204, 110, 0.3);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .examples-footer a:hover {
    color: var(--eldritch);
    border-bottom-color: var(--eldritch);
  }

  .examples-footer em {
    color: var(--void-purple);
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
